But a stress-accent like the Latin could hardly be kept from asserting itself in Roman poetry3 and, as a matter of fact, we find that the changes which the Greek metres underwent in the hands of these Roman imitators are, in many cases, clearly due to an attempt to reconcile the natural stress-accent of the words with the ictus or metrical beat of the line.
